5:
What lovely weather... Quite suitable
for taking tea outside.
9:
So uh... You're the one who hired me,
right?
13:
Yes. The name is Miguel. A pleasure
to meet you.
16:
Oh. You're a lot more easygoing
than the Guild had me believe.
20:
I'm a simple diplomat, sent to do the
Guild's bidding wherever and
whenever they need me.
23:
A diplomat... So you ARE someone
famous!
24:
Do you have a carriage waiting? I
know I'm supposed to be guarding
you, and I don't mind walking, but...
27: Well, Alk. I don't have a carriage, no.
30:
But you can't get sent wherever,
whenever, without an appropriate
ride! Hop on, and I'll show you the
world!
36:
Voluntas Arcane Arts Academy is a
vital educational institution for
Palpebra.
37:
The faculty values wisdom and skill
as much as they respect decorum.
Money isn't everything to them.
38:
Which is why I require an escort that
can keep himself polite and discreet.
43:
Most importantly, I need someone
who is considerate of others. I think
you'll do just fine.
46:
Well, well, if it isn't the Guild's
wandering messenger. Did the good
weather tempt you from your perch?
49:
My wings are always restless when
there are sights to see.
51:
You are welcome to stay as long as
you like, though I'm afraid the sights
aren't as magnificent as you might
be used to.
53:
By the way, did you happen to travel
using a familiar?
55:
You are correct. Though my familiar
may pale in comparison to the
miracles of the academy...
58: I am proud to call this one a friend.
61:
How marvelous! The engineering
behind this is astounding! What did
you use as a catalyst?!
63:
I can tell that a shape-shifting
magical item was used as the base.
Did you utilize a type of metal
manipulation magic, or...
66:
Hahaha, I'd like to ask you to keep
this a secret, but I utilized
techniques from the Kaleidoscope...
70: Man, I'm so out of place... Whyâ€”
74: Why did I choose you as my escort?
81:
It didn't take long to wrap up my
business.
84: Huh?! But we only just got here!
86:
Never mind that. Tell me, have you
ever wondered what it's like to work
outside the spotlight?
90:
What, like being a side character
instead of a main one?
92:
Exactly. You see, a clever person
should strive to operate undetected.
94:
There are countless options for
escorts out there. But I wanted to
observe YOU, speak with YOUâ€”get to
know who you are.
97:
And judging by my observations...
you make a habit of hopping
between worlds.
99:
Don't worry, I haven't told any of my
superiors yet. I wanted to see if I
could trust you first.
103: But why? What's the end goal here?
105:
I understand you're concerned, but I
promise we're here to discuss
business, not threats.
106:
I'm curious what kind of influence
you'll have on Palpebra, which is
why I'd like to remain by your side
for the time being.
108:
Just spy on me if you want to. You
can do that from a distance, thanks.
110:
What, and miss the chance to get to
know you and your companions
better?
111:
I realize my presence is a risk for you
and yours, but I can't stand idly by
when I see a potential threat to our
national interests.
114: Talk about a real convincing offer...
117:
You know I'm a man of business, Alk.
My offers never disappoint.
121:
Counteroffer: join us on our
adventures as a FRIEND. Doesn't that
sound much better?
124:
Well, if you're open to the idea. Do
you host tea parties?
127:
We can. I'll even throw in some
homemade cookies to sweeten the
deal.
130:
Then the choice has been made for
me. I look forward to working with
you, my friend.
132:
Why don't we look around? That
magical cooling tool there looks
interesting.
134:
A seasoned chef such as yourself
should find it to your liking.
138:
Wow, you've been spying on me for
a while, huh...
140:
But... you're not wrong. This thing is
kinda cool!
143: Mhmm, he is a fascinating one.
